Title: Box movement
Description:
Related to #5.
If the main character moves against a box, the box moves to the direction of the character movement only if the inmediate next square to the box is free (is not a wall).
Author: RIESGO DOS SANTOS, DANIEL

Title: Ignore wrong level maps
Description:
Related to #2.
When creating a level map it need to satisfy three requirements:
(1) there are at least one box and one goal position; (2) there is only one
warehouse man; and, (3) the board contains the same number of boxes and goal positions
Author: RIESGO DOS SANTOS, DANIEL
